# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: UnionKingdom | Scene: UnionKingdom5
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah had arrived at the staging ground."
    new "Sarah had arrived at the staging ground."

    old "All through the courtyard, there was a busy and anxious buzzing of people."
    new "All through the courtyard, there was a busy and anxious buzzing of people."

    old "Soldiers, servants, each hard at work preparing for her departure for Normandi to attend the Union Council."
    new "Soldiers, servants, each hard at work preparing for her departure for Normandi to attend the Union Council."

    old "A few days back, the royal messenger had been send back, carrying with him the message of her acceptance."
    new "A few days back, the royal messenger had been send back, carrying with him the message of her acceptance."

    old "They would know she was coming. Whatever this would prove to be, it had been set in motion."
    new "They would know she was coming. Whatever this would prove to be, it had been set in motion."

    old "Sarah found herself almost hoping for an excuse. Something to delay her departure."
    new "Sarah found herself almost hoping for an excuse. Something to delay her departure."

    old "From the corner of her eyes, she saw Varga appear."
    new "From the corner of her eyes, she saw Varga appear."

    old "Her husband."
    new "Her husband."

    old "Stoic as always, though she knew to read his face well enough to see the soft cracks."
    new "Stoic as always, though she knew to read his face well enough to see the soft cracks."

    old "I see they are nearly ready."
    new "I see they are nearly ready."

    old "Stating facts rather than emotion. She loved his grounded emotions, almost as much as she hated it."
    new "Stating facts rather than emotion. She loved his grounded emotions, almost as much as she hated it."

    old "Yes, it won't be long now before the captain of the guard declares we are ready."
    new "Yes, it won't be long now before the captain of the guard declares we are ready."

    old "Sarah saw more crates of supplies being carried onto the wagons."
    new "Sarah saw more crates of supplies being carried onto the wagons."

    old "The trip to Normandi was not impossible far, little over a week, but with an entourage like this they would require provisions."
    new "The trip to Normandi was not impossible far, little over a week, but with an entourage like this they would require provisions."

    old "I told these two we could wave you out from atop the ramparts, but they insisted to see you in person."
    new "I told these two we could wave you out from atop the ramparts, but they insisted to see you in person."

    old "Sarah could see her son and daughter, clinging to their father's legs, hiding behind him."
    new "Sarah could see her son and daughter, clinging to their father's legs, hiding behind him."

    old "Sarah kneeled down and smiled."
    new "Sarah kneeled down and smiled."

    old "Is that so?"
    new "Is that so?"

    old "You know I'll be back in less than a month, right?"
    new "You know I'll be back in less than a month, right?"

    old "Sarah could see Miriam, her daughter, begin to sob."
    new "Sarah could see Miriam, her daughter, begin to sob."

    old "Ooh, hey, don't cry. Come here."
    new "Ooh, hey, don't cry. Come here."

    old "Sarah opened her arms and Miriam jumped into the embrace."
    new "Sarah opened her arms and Miriam jumped into the embrace."

    old "Orwen, her son, older by a few years than his sister and pretending to be stronger than he was, held back for a moment."
    new "Orwen, her son, older by a few years than his sister and pretending to be stronger than he was, held back for a moment."

    old "You too, Orwen, come here."
    new "You too, Orwen, come here."

    old "At his mother's invitation, he jumped into her arms."
    new "At his mother's invitation, he jumped into her arms."

    old "For a while, Sarah endured their sobbing."
    new "For a while, Sarah endured their sobbing."

    old "Their father had left more then a few times, relating to his duties as Warmaster."
    new "Their father had left more then a few times, relating to his duties as Warmaster."

    old "Over time, they had come to get used to that."
    new "Over time, they had come to get used to that."

    old "But their mother leaving was a new fact, and like all new things, the children were quickly uneased by them."
    new "But their mother leaving was a new fact, and like all new things, the children were quickly uneased by them."

    old "Slowly, the sobbing quieted and Sarah released them both from her arms."
    new "Slowly, the sobbing quieted and Sarah released them both from her arms."

    old "There, now don't be too sad, alright?"
    new "There, now don't be too sad, alright?"

    old "Dad is right here and he's not going anywhere. He'll keep you safe. And I'll be back before you know it, promise."
    new "Dad is right here and he's not going anywhere. He'll keep you safe. And I'll be back before you know it, promise."

    old "Is it dangerous?"
    new "Is it dangerous?"

    old "Sarah smiled, making sure not to show a moment of doubt."
    new "Sarah smiled, making sure not to show a moment of doubt."

    old "No, I'm just going to visit my friend, Queen Maeiv. We're going to talk, and then I'll be home again."
    new "No, I'm just going to visit my friend, Queen Maeiv. We're going to talk, and then I'll be home again."

    old "Talk about what?"
    new "Talk about what?"

    old "Grown-up things, very boring. You want me to tell you?"
    new "Grown-up things, very boring. You want me to tell you?"

    old "Hearing that the matters were in the realm of grown-ups, her daughter quickly shook her head, fearing to be bored."
    new "Hearing that the matters were in the realm of grown-ups, her daughter quickly shook her head, fearing to be bored."

    old "She turned to her son."
    new "She turned to her son."

    old "Now Orwen."
    new "Now Orwen."

    old "He stood to attention, as if the world's smallest soldier."
    new "He stood to attention, as if the world's smallest soldier."

    old "You promise to look out for your sister, and not give your father too much trouble?"
    new "You promise to look out for your sister, and not give your father too much trouble?"

    old "I promise!"
    new "I promise!"

    old "Sarah watched Varga reach down and tossle the boy's hair."
    new "Sarah watched Varga reach down and tossle the boy's hair."

    old "Hey, don't go making promises to your mom that you can't keep."
    new "Hey, don't go making promises to your mom that you can't keep."

    old "You're always trouble."
    new "You're always trouble."

    old "Sarah watched as Orwen jumped up and grabbed for his father, who quickly pulled him into a wrestling match that the boy had no chance of winning."
    new "Sarah watched as Orwen jumped up and grabbed for his father, who quickly pulled him into a wrestling match that the boy had no chance of winning."

    old "Watching like this, she saw her family and all she left behind."
    new "Watching like this, she saw her family and all she left behind."

    old "More than ever, Sarah now wished for her own safe return."
    new "More than ever, Sarah now wished for her own safe return."

    old "As Varga dropped Orwen back down and held Miriam aside, the two had the briefest moment of privacy."
    new "As Varga dropped Orwen back down and held Miriam aside, the two had the briefest moment of privacy."

    old "Promise me you won't do anything risky."
    new "Promise me you won't do anything risky."

    old "I thought you loved me for being risky."
    new "I thought you loved me for being risky."

    old "I always knew that hoping you to change would be a fools effort."
    new "I always knew that hoping you to change would be a fools effort."

    old "But please..."
    new "But please..."

    old "His voice was soft, and contained in it, his pleading for a promise."
    new "His voice was soft, and contained in it, his pleading for a promise."

    old "I will come back to you. All of you."
    new "I will come back to you. All of you."

    old "Her eyes drifted to their children."
    new "Her eyes drifted to their children."

    old "If only because these two would be the end of you without me."
    new "If only because these two would be the end of you without me."

    old "Her husband smiled and they kissed and embraced."
    new "Her husband smiled and they kissed and embraced."

    old "Sarah waved as Varga seized their children and carried them off, allowing her to focus back on her impending departure."
    new "Sarah waved as Varga seized their children and carried them off, allowing her to focus back on her impending departure."

    old "Her Warmaster."
    new "Her Warmaster."

    old "Stoic as always."
    new "Stoic as always."

    old "I see you're almost ready."
    new "I see you're almost ready."

    old "Won't be long now before the captain of the guard declares that we are ready to leave."
    new "Won't be long now before the captain of the guard declares that we are ready to leave."

    old "Varga inspected the wagons from a distance."
    new "Varga inspected the wagons from a distance."

    old "They're all capable men, I've made sure of it."
    new "They're all capable men, I've made sure of it."

    old "I would expect nothing less of my Warmster."
    new "I would expect nothing less of my Warmster."

    old "He looked proud at the compliment."
    new "He looked proud at the compliment."

    old "Sarah...if you ask, I can still come along."
    new "Sarah...if you ask, I can still come along."

    old "Your offer is kind, but you will be needed here."
    new "Your offer is kind, but you will be needed here."

    old "Trust that you are serving me best in your current station."
    new "Trust that you are serving me best in your current station."

    old "But if they so much as harm a hair on your head..."
    new "But if they so much as harm a hair on your head..."

    old "Then war."
    new "Then war."

    old "He paused for a moment, then nodded sternly."
    new "He paused for a moment, then nodded sternly."

    old "A silence lingered a moment longer."
    new "A silence lingered a moment longer."

    old "Sarah prayed that it would not come to that."
    new "Sarah prayed that it would not come to that."

    old "Thank you, Varga."
    new "Thank you, Varga."

    old "Thank you for everything you've done in supporting me."
    new "Thank you for everything you've done in supporting me."

    old "I could never have asked for a more loyal friend."
    new "I could never have asked for a more loyal friend."

    old "And I could ask for no greater praise. All I ask is the same any of us ask. Come back to us."
    new "And I could ask for no greater praise. All I ask is the same any of us ask. Come back to us."

    old "Sarah placed a hand over her heart."
    new "Sarah placed a hand over her heart."

    old "I swear I will."
    new "I swear I will."

    old "With it, the two said the last of their goodbyes and Sarah watched Varga depart."
    new "With it, the two said the last of their goodbyes and Sarah watched Varga depart."

    old "Sarah turned as she suddenly saw her brother approach."
    new "Sarah turned as she suddenly saw her brother approach."

    old "Aah, time out of your many books to come and give your dear sister a goodbye?"
    new "Aah, time out of your many books to come and give your dear sister a goodbye?"

    old "All these people are worried about you."
    new "All these people are worried about you."

    old "I might be the only one who knows that it's Queen Maeiv who should be worried."
    new "I might be the only one who knows that it's Queen Maeiv who should be worried."

    old "Sarah gestured at backpack that rested near her brother's feet."
    new "Sarah gestured at backpack that rested near her brother's feet."

    old "What's that?"
    new "What's that?"

    old "My gift. Or as close as one as I could manage."
    new "My gift. Or as close as one as I could manage."

    old "It's all the books that I could find on recent Normandi history."
    new "It's all the books that I could find on recent Normandi history."

    old "Knowledge is its own form of power."
    new "Knowledge is its own form of power."

    old "Thank you, Thomas. It's very kind."
    new "Thank you, Thomas. It's very kind."

    old "She motioned for one of the servants to carry it onto the wagons."
    new "She motioned for one of the servants to carry it onto the wagons."

    old "I'll promise to read as much of it as I can."
    new "I'll promise to read as much of it as I can."

    old "At least I'll have something to do on the road there."
    new "At least I'll have something to do on the road there."

    old "She saw Thomas study the wagons."
    new "She saw Thomas study the wagons."

    old "You won't forget to look out for yourself while I'm gone?"
    new "You won't forget to look out for yourself while I'm gone?"

    old "Her brother seemed flustered."
    new "Her brother seemed flustered."

    old "What are you talking about?"
    new "What are you talking about?"

    old "I've had to pick you off the library floor more than a few times."
    new "I've had to pick you off the library floor more than a few times."

    old "Oh, that..."
    new "Oh, that..."

    old "Yes, that! I'm not asking you to change, Thomas, but you also can't live like a recluse."
    new "Yes, that! I'm not asking you to change, Thomas, but you also can't live like a recluse."

    old "You have people who love you. More than just me."
    new "You have people who love you. More than just me."

    old "I know, I'll...do my best."
    new "I know, I'll...do my best."

    old "I guess that's about all I can ask of you."
    new "I guess that's about all I can ask of you."

    old "She suddenly poked her brother underneath his ribs."
    new "She suddenly poked her brother underneath his ribs."

    old "And go meet with some of those girls from the party. I've had their mothers complain you won't even meet with them."
    new "And go meet with some of those girls from the party. I've had their mothers complain you won't even meet with them."

    old "What? All I'm asking is for you to meet with them. It will do you good."
    new "What? All I'm asking is for you to meet with them. It will do you good."

    old "Waste my time on a stroll in the gardens?"
    new "Waste my time on a stroll in the gardens?"

    old "The sun alone will do you good."
    new "The sun alone will do you good."

    old "Besides, some of these girls are more like you than you'd think."
    new "Besides, some of these girls are more like you than you'd think."

    old "According to her mother, Lady Arison spends nearly as much time in the library as you do."
    new "According to her mother, Lady Arison spends nearly as much time in the library as you do."

    old "Thomas rolled his eyes."
    new "Thomas rolled his eyes."

    old "You can go and...I don't know, sit and read in silence next to each other."
    new "You can go and...I don't know, sit and read in silence next to each other."

    old "That actually doesn't sound as bad as you make it out to be."
    new "That actually doesn't sound as bad as you make it out to be."

    old "Promise me you'll try?"
    new "Promise me you'll try?"

    old "Thomas sighed and nodded."
    new "Thomas sighed and nodded."

    old "Yes, Sarah. I promise. But if you don't make it back home, I promise I'll marry to the worst of them all, so you'd better come home."
    new "Yes, Sarah. I promise. But if you don't make it back home, I promise I'll marry to the worst of them all, so you'd better come home."

    old "Sarah suddenly rushed forward and hugged her brother."
    new "Sarah suddenly rushed forward and hugged her brother."

    old "She felt him slowly returning the hug, awkwardly."
    new "She felt him slowly returning the hug, awkwardly."

    old "The two siblings stood in embrace for a short while before they broke."
    new "The two siblings stood in embrace for a short while before they broke."

    old "Sarah looked at her brother."
    new "Sarah looked at her brother."

    old "She truly hoped he'd be alright."
    new "She truly hoped he'd be alright."

    old "Sarah and Thomas exchanged the last of their words and Sarah watched as her brother turned and left."
    new "Sarah and Thomas exchanged the last of their words and Sarah watched as her brother turned and left."

    old "Studying the wagons, Sarah could see that they were nearly ready for departure."
    new "Studying the wagons, Sarah could see that they were nearly ready for departure."

    old "She had put it all off as long as she could."
    new "She had put it all off as long as she could."

    old "Looking around the walls of Castle Reinmeer, she tried to take it all in."
    new "Looking around the walls of Castle Reinmeer, she tried to take it all in."

    old "This place had been the center of her life for so many years now..."
    new "This place had been the center of her life for so many years now..."

    old "Leaving it felt almost alien, especially considering how many people she left behind."
    new "Leaving it felt almost alien, especially considering how many people she left behind."

    old "But they would wait for her."
    new "But they would wait for her."

    old "And she would wait for the hour of her return, to see them all again."
    new "And she would wait for the hour of her return, to see them all again."

    old "She committed herself to the thought, as if to will it into reality."
    new "She committed herself to the thought, as if to will it into reality."

    old "Sarah saw Lily walk up to her."
    new "Sarah saw Lily walk up to her."

    old "Nearly ready, I think."
    new "Nearly ready, I think."

    old "Sarah nodded and smiled."
    new "Sarah nodded and smiled."

    old "She was happy that Lily would join her."
    new "She was happy that Lily would join her."

    old "Perhaps even more just for the company than her skill with a blade."
    new "Perhaps even more just for the company than her skill with a blade."

    old "I'm glad you're here with me."
    new "I'm glad you're here with me."

    old "Sarah watched as Lily awkwardly tried to hide her own smile."
    new "Sarah watched as Lily awkwardly tried to hide her own smile."

    old "I'm just keeping my vow..."
    new "I'm just keeping my vow..."

    old "Ah, the unquestionable honor of Lily Hightower, fear those who might besmirch it."
    new "Ah, the unquestionable honor of Lily Hightower, fear those who might besmirch it."

    old "Hey, if you're gonna act like a-"
    new "Hey, if you're gonna act like a-"

    old "A what? Mind what you call the ruler of this country."
    new "A what? Mind what you call the ruler of this country."

    old "She saw Lily grin."
    new "She saw Lily grin."

    old "Well...whatever I was going to call you, it has now slipped my mind."
    new "Well...whatever I was going to call you, it has now slipped my mind."

    old "That's what I thought."
    new "That's what I thought."

    old "The two women laughed, breaking their pretend feud."
    new "The two women laughed, breaking their pretend feud."

    old "I think I'll have to talk to the captain about my seating."
    new "I think I'll have to talk to the captain about my seating."

    old "Your seating?"
    new "Your seating?"

    old "On the wagon, yeah."
    new "On the wagon, yeah."

    old "Oh Lily, please. You're riding with me in the main carriage."
    new "Oh Lily, please. You're riding with me in the main carriage."

    old "It's really no problem, I can-"
    new "It's really no problem, I can-"

    old "Sarah threw up a hand and ended the discussion."
    new "Sarah threw up a hand and ended the discussion."

    old "Your my bodyguard, so you'll have to be close if anything happens, right?"
    new "Your my bodyguard, so you'll have to be close if anything happens, right?"

    old "Yeah, but-"
    new "Yeah, but-"

    old "Good. And the whole trip is more than a week."
    new "Good. And the whole trip is more than a week."

    old "What else am I going to do, stare out the window? I need someone to talk to or I'll go mad."
    new "What else am I going to do, stare out the window? I need someone to talk to or I'll go mad."

    old "What? Can't the soldiers make for conversation?"
    new "What? Can't the soldiers make for conversation?"

    old "Oh, they're very good at their jobs, but their jobs don't require being great conversationalists."
    new "Oh, they're very good at their jobs, but their jobs don't require being great conversationalists."

    old "Alright then, I'll ride with you."
    new "Alright then, I'll ride with you."

    old "For your protection, of course."
    new "For your protection, of course."

    old "Of course."
    new "Of course."

    old "Sarah watched as Lily was called away by one of the soldiers, attending to some task on one of the wagons."
    new "Sarah watched as Lily was called away by one of the soldiers, attending to some task on one of the wagons."

    old "Looking out over all the business, it all struck Sarah as somewhat of a beehive."
    new "Looking out over all the business, it all struck Sarah as somewhat of a beehive."

    old "A busy, chaotic, almost maddening scene."
    new "A busy, chaotic, almost maddening scene."

    old "And yet..."
    new "And yet..."

    old "Among it all, some kind of order, even if the individual elements of that order couldn't see it, or even realize it."
    new "Among it all, some kind of order, even if the individual elements of that order couldn't see it, or even realize it."

    old "She smiled as the last of the preparations were carried out."
    new "She smiled as the last of the preparations were carried out."

    old "Then, as she had hoped yet equally feared, the captain of the guard called out."
    new "Then, as she had hoped yet equally feared, the captain of the guard called out."

    old "Ready to depart at your order!"
    new "Ready to depart at your order!"

    old "All eyes fell on her as the courtyard went quiet."
    new "All eyes fell on her as the courtyard went quiet."

    old "Sarah walked towards the carriage. Each step felt like one closer to her doom."
    new "Sarah walked towards the carriage. Each step felt like one closer to her doom."

    old "She shook her head."
    new "She shook her head."

    old "She needed to exhude strength, now more than ever."
    new "She needed to exhude strength, now more than ever."

    old "Sarah stepped into the carriage."
    new "Sarah stepped into the carriage."

    old "When the door fell shut, she looked out over the sea of faces."
    new "When the door fell shut, she looked out over the sea of faces."

    old "It had gone quiet, not so segregated from the outside world."
    new "It had gone quiet, not so segregated from the outside world."

    old "She saw some of the servants clasp their hands in prayer."
    new "She saw some of the servants clasp their hands in prayer."

    old "The soldiers saluted."
    new "The soldiers saluted."

    old "Then, the carts shook and began to move."
    new "Then, the carts shook and began to move."

    old "At first slow, but quickly gathering speed."
    new "At first slow, but quickly gathering speed."

    old "The world she knew and had grown up in, dissapeared behind her."
    new "The world she knew and had grown up in, dissapeared behind her."

    old "From castle to city, to the city gates, and then out onto the open road."
    new "From castle to city, to the city gates, and then out onto the open road."

    old "Sarah watched the world transform as she was carried off towards an uncertain place."
    new "Sarah watched the world transform as she was carried off towards an uncertain place."

